VT4(The 'reverse test' - also known as the 'physical to book' test - is conducted to determine whether assets 'physically' selected from the office floor can be located in e-AMT (the 'book').
This procedure is called by the Verifying Assets - Testing Procedure when the 'IT Fixed Assets - Forward Test Sample' is sent by ADL Business Operations to the Location IT Fixed Asset Tester. At this time, ADL Business Operations also advises which Locations have been randomly selected for 'reverse testing' (physical to book) and the number of assets that are to be tested in the current testing period.
Perform a walkaround of your location and randomly select the stipulated number of assets from the office floor - including the machine room/s, interior office areas and open office areas - that is, all areas where Lab-owned equipment is located. Proceed to 02. )
VT4(In the workbook, record the name of the Asset Owner, the machine type and the machine serial number for each of the randomly selected assets. Proceed to 03.)

VT4(For each randomly selected asset for testing, check whether the item is listed in e-AMT.
If Yes - the asset is located in e-AMT, proceed to 08. If No - the asset cannot be located in e-AMT, proceed to 04.
Important Note: Steps 03 to 12 are repeated for each of the assets you select. )

VT4(Determine if the Asset Owner can provide acceptable verification evidence that the asset is new. Acceptable evidence of a new asset is: a) Copy of delivery information showing the asset has been delivered within 90 days of the current date; AND b) Screen capture or other evidence that the Establish Asset Procedure has been initiated within 90 days of asset delivery. If Yes - the verification evidence has been obtained and is acceptable, send the evidence to ADL Business Operations, then proceed to 08. If No - the verification evidence cannot be obtained, proceed to 06. )

VT4(Where the asset cannot be located in e-AMT, ask the Asset Owner to immediately initiate the Establish Asset Procedure, and ensure the Asset Owner's line manager is copied on the request. Proceed to 07. )

VT4(In the workbook, record the asset as 'Unlocated' and advise ADL Business Operations of the circumstances around the defect, noting all procedures that have been initiated to add the asset to e-AMT. Proceed to 09. )
VT4(Obtain verification evidence & record the asset as 'Located'; OR Record the asset as 'Unlocated'.)
VT4(Verification results recorded in the IT Fixed Assets - Reverse Test workbook and sent to ADL Business Operations upon completion (workbook is stored in the Business Process Testing Repository): )

VT4(In the workbook, record the asset as 'Located' and retain either: a) Evidence of the e-AMT verification; OR b) Evidence that the asset is 'new' (as detailed in step 05, above). Acceptable evidence of physical verification includes: a) Physical verification by the Location IT Fixed Asset Tester; OR b) Screen capture of the system BIOS showing the asset serial number; OR c) Photograph of the asset serial number; OR d) Written verification by a manager who has physically verified the asset.
Proceed to 09. )
VT4(Obtain verification evidence & record the asset as 'Located'; OR Record the asset as 'Unlocated'.)
VT4(Verification results recorded in the IT Fixed Assets - Reverse Test workbook and sent to ADL Business Operations upon completion (workbook is stored in the Business Process Testing Repository): )
VT4(Where the asset information in e-AMT is not accurate, ask the Asset Owner to immediately initiate the e-AMT Update Asset Information Procedure. Proceed to 11.)

VT4(In the Sample file, record the asset information as 'Correct' and retain evidence of the information integrity verification. The asset information listed in e-AMT that must be verified is: a) Asset Owner; AND b) Machine Type; AND c) Machine Serial Number; AND d) Asset Location (Work Location & Building).
Note: The following fields should also be verified during the test, however, are not considered defects if incorrect and are not measured (remediation is, however, still required to ensure the accuracy of e-AMT): Location Type; Floor; Room Number; Property Control Usage Code; and Asset Description. Proceed to 13. )

VT4(Verification results recorded in the IT Fixed Assets - Reverse Test workbook and sent to ADL Business Operations upon completion (workbook is stored in the Business Process Testing Repository): Result of 'information integrity test' to determine the accuracy of the asset information stored in e-AMT. Asset information that must be verified: a) Asset Owner; AND b) Machine Type; AND c) Machine Serial Number; AND d) Asset Location (Work Location & Building). Note: The following fields should also be verified during the test, however, are not considered defects if incorrect and are not measured (remediation is, however, still required to ensure accuracy of e-AMT): Location Type; Floor; Room Number; Property Control Usage Code; and Asset Description. Target: 95% of asset records are accurate. )

VT4(In the workbook, record the asset information as 'Incorrect' and advise ADL Business Operations of the circumstances around the defect, noting all procedures that have been initiated to correct the asset information. Proceed to 13.)

VT4(Verification results recorded in the IT Fixed Assets - Reverse Test workbook and sent to ADL Business Operations upon completion (workbook is stored in the Business Process Testing Repository): Result of 'information integrity test' to determine the accuracy of the asset information stored in e-AMT. Asset information that must be verified: a) Asset Owner; AND b) Machine Type; AND c) Machine Serial Number; AND d) Asset Location (Work Location & Building). Note: The following fields should also be verified during the test, however, are not considered defects if incorrect and are not measured (remediation is, however, still required to ensure accuracy of e-AMT): Location Type; Floor; Room Number; Property Control Usage Code; and Asset Description. Target: 95% of asset records are accurate. )

VT4(Send a copy of the completed workbook to ADL Business Operations with the defect assets identified, advising the circumstances around each defect, and noting all procedures that have been initiated to remediate the defects. Proceed to 15. (The procedure also proceeds to 17).)

VT4(pon receipt of the workbook identifying any assets found with defects during the reverse testing, locate the 'Defect Control' worksheet in the IT Fixed Assets Report for the current testing period. Insert the asset and defect details. The recorded defects will be tracked to closure. The procedure ends.)
